'''Maik Bullmann''' (born April 25, 1967 in [[Frankfurt an der Oder]]) is a [[Germany|German]] [[wrestling|wrestler]], Olympic champion in [[Greco-Roman wrestling]], and three times world champion.

==Olympics==
Bullmann competed at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]] where he received a gold medal in [[Greco-Roman wrestling]], the ''light heavyweight'' class.<ref name=db-ol-WRE1992>[http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=23&sp=WRE "1992 Summer Olympics &ndash; Barcelona, Spain &ndash; Wrestling"] ''databaseOlympics.com''<small> (Retrieved on August 28, 2008)</small></ref>

He received a bronze medal at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta]]. 

==World championships==
Bullmann won a gold medal at the [[1989 FILA Wrestling World Championships]], and again [[1990 FILA Wrestling World Championships|in 1990]] and [[1991 FILA Wrestling World Championships|in 1991]].

==Awards==
He was awarded the [[Bambi (prize)|Bambi prize]] in 1992.

